<pre><code>#include &lt;iostream&gt; using namespace std;  int main(int argc, char *argv[]) {     int x = 0, y = 1, k = 5; {            int x = 1;     x = 10;     cout &lt;&lt; "x is " &lt;&lt; x &lt;&lt; ", y is " &lt;&lt; y &lt;&lt; endl;      } cout &lt;&lt; "x is " &lt;&lt; x &lt;&lt; " and k is " &lt;&lt; k &lt;&lt; endl;  cout &lt;&lt; endl; cout &lt;&lt; endl; {     int x = 5;     int y = 6;     {         int y = 7;         x = 2;     }     cout &lt;&lt; "(x, y) is : (" &lt;&lt; x &lt;&lt; ", " &lt;&lt; y &lt;&lt; ")" &lt;&lt; endl; }   cin.get(); return 0; } </code></pre>  <p>The output is:</p>  <p>x is 10, y is 1</p>  <p>x is 0 and k is 5</p>  <p>(x, y) is : (2, 6)</p>  <p>I think (x,y) should be (5,6). Because that's the coordinates x and y are in.</p>